Formalizes Police Special Services Unit. The Federal Executive Council (FEC) has approved the award of a contract to Dangote group for the construction of five roads totaling 274.9 kilometres at the local cost of N309.9billion to be advanced by the company as tax credit. Minister of Works and Housing, Babatunde Fashola, who disclosed this at the end of the council meeting presided over by President Muhammadu Buhari at the presidential villa, Abuja explained that the move is also part of the governmentâ€™s multiple funding options with the private sector. The roads are located between Bama and Banke in Borno State, the Nnamdi Azikiwe road in Kaduna State and the Deep Sea Port access road, sections one and three in Lagos State through the Epe to Sagamu expressway. Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that Senior Special Assistant to the President (Media & Publicity), Mallam Garba Shehu, also spoke on the memos presented by some ministers also approved by FEC including the formalization of the Police Special Service Unit operated through a private-public partnership in the interest of transparency and accountability.  Mallam Garba said Council also approved contracts worth N754million for the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) for capital projects.